{"id":"mai-06yi","kind":"ticket","type":"feature","title":"mai search — BM25 full-text search over notes","priority":1,"tags":["feature","search","bm25"],"body":"## What\n\nAdd `mai search \u003cquery\u003e` command. BM25 full-text search over all notes (tickets, docs, decisions, artifacts, PRs, reviews). No external dependencies. Computed during Index.Build(), scored at query time.\n\n## Context\n\nConversation with hooman 2026-04-04:\n- Discovered mai has no full-text search capability\n- Ticket content lives in git objects (refs/notes/maitake), accessible but unsearchable\n- Prototyped BM25 in Python: excellent quality on maitake (73 tickets) and trek (5192 tickets, 180MB text)\n- Quality confirmed on 5 diverse queries: molten lava, hot cold warm state, smooth gameplay, macro generator, boundary calls\n- Python tokenize+score: ~6s on 5k tickets. Go estimate: \u003c50ms.\n- cs (codespelunker) validates the brute-force-no-index approach at much larger scale\n- Index.Build() already walks all States — adding tokenization is free ride\n- Cache lifecycle handles invalidation automatically (keyed by ref tip SHA)\n\n## Architecture Decision\n\n- Lives in pkg/notes/search.go (same layer as Index.Query)\n- TextIndex built during Index.Build() — zero extra lifecycle management\n- Weighted fields: title=3.0, tags=2.0, body=1.0, comments=0.5\n- Composes with existing FindOptions for kind/status/tag filtering\n- Engine interface gets Search() method\n- CLI subcommand in cmd/mai/main.go\n- No external deps — tokenizer is strings.FieldsFunc + toLower\n- No stemming in v1 (YAGNI — prototype proves raw tokens work great)\n\n## Implementation (TDD)\n\n### Phase 1: BM25 scorer (pkg/notes/search.go + search_test.go)\n- [ ] Test: BM25 scores empty corpus → no results\n- [ ] Test: BM25 single doc, single term match → positive score\n- [ ] Test: BM25 term frequency boosts score (more occurrences = higher)\n- [ ] Test: BM25 IDF — rare terms score higher than common terms\n- [ ] Test: BM25 doc length normalization — short doc with match beats long doc\n- [ ] Test: BM25 multi-term query scores sum correctly\n- [ ] Test: BM25 no-match terms → zero score\n- [ ] Test: top-K returns ranked results, limited\n\n### Phase 2: TextIndex + Index.Build integration\n- [ ] Test: TextIndex built from States has correct doc count\n- [ ] Test: TextIndex tokenizes title, body, tags, comments\n- [ ] Test: Field weighting — title match scores higher than comment match\n- [ ] Test: Index.Search returns SearchResults with IDs and scores\n- [ ] Test: Index.Search with FindOptions filters (kind, status, tag)\n- [ ] Test: Index.Search with empty query → no results\n- [ ] Test: Index.Search after Ingest+Build includes new note\n\n### Phase 3: Engine.Search + CLI\n- [ ] Test: RealEngine.Search delegates to index\n- [ ] Integration test: mai search \u003cquery\u003e returns ranked output\n- [ ] Integration test: mai search --json returns JSON array\n- [ ] Integration test: mai search -k ticket filters by kind\n- [ ] Integration test: mai search --status open filters by status\n- [ ] Integration test: mai search with no matches → \"No matches.\"\n\n## CLI Shape\n\n```\nmai search \"boundary calls\"                  # search everything\nmai search \"boundary calls\" -k ticket        # only tickets\nmai search \"lava planet\" -k doc              # only docs\nmai search \"pr merge\" --status open          # only open\nmai search \"macro generator\" --limit 5       # top 5\nmai search --json \"query\"                    # JSON output\n```\n\n## Types\n\n```go\ntype SearchOptions struct {\n    FindOptions\n    Limit int // default 20\n}\n\ntype SearchResult struct {\n    ID    string   `json:\"id\"`\n    Score float64  `json:\"score\"`\n    State *State   `json:\"state\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Performance Budget\n- Build text index: \u003c50ms for 5k docs\n- Search query: \u003c10ms for 5k docs\n- Total mai search: dominated by git/cache load, not scoring\n\n## Goal\n## What\n\nAdd `mai search \u003cquery\u003e` command. BM25 full-text search over all notes (tickets, docs, decisions, artifacts, PRs, reviews). No external dependencies. Computed during Index.Build(), scored at query time.\n\n## Context\n\nConversation with hooman 2026-04-04:\n- Discovered mai has no full-text search capability\n- Ticket content lives in git objects (refs/notes/maitake), accessible but unsearchable\n- Prototyped BM25 in Python: excellent quality on maitake (73 tickets) and trek (5192 tickets, 180MB text)\n- Quality confirmed on 5 diverse queries: molten lava, hot cold warm state, smooth gameplay, macro generator, boundary calls\n- Python tokenize+score: ~6s on 5k tickets. Go estimate: \u003c50ms.\n- cs (codespelunker) validates the brute-force-no-index approach at much larger scale\n- Index.Build() already walks all States — adding tokenization is free ride\n- Cache lifecycle handles invalidation automatically (keyed by ref tip SHA)\n\n## Architecture Decision\n\n- Lives in pkg/notes/search.go (same layer as Index.Query)\n- TextIndex built during Index.Build() — zero extra lifecycle management\n- Weighted fields: title=3.0, tags=2.0, body=1.0, comments=0.5\n- Composes with existing FindOptions for kind/status/tag filtering\n- Engine interface gets Search() method\n- CLI subcommand in cmd/mai/main.go\n- No external deps — tokenizer is strings.FieldsFunc + toLower\n- No stemming in v1 (YAGNI — prototype proves raw tokens work great)\n\n## Implementation (TDD)\n\n### Phase 1: BM25 scorer (pkg/notes/search.go + search_test.go)\n- [ ] Test: BM25 scores empty corpus → no results\n- [ ] Test: BM25 single doc, single term match → positive score\n- [ ] Test: BM25 term frequency boosts score (more occurrences = higher)\n- [ ] Test: BM25 IDF — rare terms score higher than common terms\n- [ ] Test: BM25 doc length normalization — short doc with match beats long doc\n- [ ] Test: BM25 multi-term query scores sum correctly\n- [ ] Test: BM25 no-match terms → zero score\n- [ ] Test: top